{
  "texts": [
    "In these cases, the rule of thumb could lead to unnecessarily screening too many records, but at the same time makes the SAFE procedure more conservative.",
    "Researchers should exercise caution and use appropriate statistical methods to estimate the fraction of relevant records when working with small datasets.",
    "When resources are not an issue, in some cases, it might be equally suitable to screen the whole set manually.",
    "Furthermore, the proposed batch size for the number of irrelevant records in a row depends on the research question, the domain of the review, and the desired level of recall.",
    "For example, in the field of medicine, missing any relevant records might not be acceptable, so a larger batch size is advised."
  ]
}